That being said: I don't know how frequently the menu rotates, so maybe I just hit a day without those items.  Some complex choices on the menu. Francesca's Bryn Mawr is our favorite restaurant, one which we have fully enjoyed for many years. From their thoughtfully beginning every meal with fresh, warm, crusty bread and olive oil to all of their delightful, freshly prepared foods through house made desserts and scrumptious, creamy gelato and Italian coffees and espressos,  every aspect of the meal is far above average. Daily specials help fight ennui. Their full bar is well staffed by pros. The wine list is very good and well rounded. Servers are thoughtful and efficient. Decor is warmly modern. The outdoor area is about as good as possible in their situation.  There is no better spot for an intimate meal or a good sized party.  We very highly recommend Francesca's on Bryn Mawr. We have unfailingly been made happy here every time we have visited.

For such a nice place, you'd expect better service and attention, even if it's only a table for two.

Horrible Horrible Horrible. Came in last Thursday to have dinner with my mother. Live in the neighborhood and walk past this place every day. So we arrive at 5:50 PM right in time before happy hour ended. The server comes over at 5:55 PM so we're limited on time and placed drink orders and a salad. I asked if they had Italian dressing or plain vinegar and oil due to allergy to dairy/white creams. Serve said no and walked off. So when he came back I told him I would do lemon and oil but was shocked that they didn't have red wine vinegar. So time to order food so we asked for angel pasta with meat sauce. Server informed us that meat sauce was made with cream. My mother proceeds to ask if the chef could make it without cream or was there any red sauces without cream. Server says "no very rudely" as if we were a bother due to our allergy. Server refused to help or come up with any suggestions to help accommodate. I've never been to a Italian restaurant or any establishment that cared about new customers not try to find a resolution. Manager never came by as he was to busy chatting it up with his white counterparts. We decided to leave and close out on the drinks and received a nasty attitude from the server. He walks off aggressively and told the manager who gave us a dirty look but still never once stopped by to fix the issue. Needless to say we will never be back and realized our color wasn't on the welcomed agenda!!!

The staff is courteous  and friendly, and knowledgeable of the items served. The waiters are well able to make excellent food and wine recommendations. The menu offers a wide variety of Italian dishes and, of course, there is also pizza. The service is prompt. The food is delicious, and the presentation makes it also a feast for the eyes. The only negative point is the 80s rock music that makes the acoustic background. It is grating and prevents a truly relaxed, cozy atmosphere. In my opinion low classical  music (Baroque) or jazz would be so much more appropriate. Of course, the peffect Italian touch would be Italian music. I found the music so annoying that I gave 4 instead of an otherwise deservedly 5 points rating.

Tasty brunch!
Had a fantastic Valentine's Dinner here.
I love that the menu changes so often and the atmosphere is great. The food is always excellent.
Great happy hour bar menu!

Ordered carry out from the Bryn Mawr location. Spoke with Charlie and got the pollo al limone. Dish was fantastic. What made my night was the fact Charlie threw in a free Tiramisu ($8) and order of pasta ($4) all on the house. This was almost the entire value of my meal! Caught me totally off-guard. I was blown away at the customer service. Great food. Great value. Great people. Thanks again
good food

The beef carpaccio happy hour special and professional staff keep me coming back when I am in the area.  The other parts of the menu I have explored have all been pleasant and each "extra pepper" type of request has been met with cheerful willingness.  When I have stopped in alone I have always found good conversation and when dining otherwise have always left pleased.  The Happy Hour specials are my lure.

This place functions like a well-oiled machine. The service was fantastic! I can't begin to express how efficient they were. Also, more importantly, the food was delicious. It was everything I was hoping for and it immediately hit the spot.
Nice food, but not super impressive! Service is slow, and not good. I prefer the branch in the downtown because the service there was amazing. Not a lot of options when it comes to sticks!

Excellant food. Their calamari is incredible. They are a little pricey as are most Italian restaurants any more. The only parking in the area is metered street parking which can be challenging at certain times in the day. The service is very well timed and the staff is very helpful.
Went here for dinner during restaurant week 2016 and truly enjoyed my meal and service!!
Service was excellent... The Samoan I had was excellent

I've been to a couple of Francesca's restaurants and this one is definitely toward the top of the list. I went here with my girlfriend and her mom to visit with some friends on a Monday and it wasn't too busy, so we received some extra …
The food and service here were good. Nothing too special, in my opinion.  They were very flexible with our reservation, though, as my date was half an hour late.

My friend took me here for a quick bite and drink. We loved it. Cocktails were good, we had mussels and apple pie  (don't remember the real name) omg so good. Warm crusty bread was the deal breaker. I will try for lunch. A must if you are in the area. Great service too.

absolutely love this place... me and my wife went here after we got married... they took very good care of us. So Francesca will be me and my wife yearly tradition for our anniversary. Great customer service and even better food.

My wife and I used to go here consistently for a dinner when neither of us wanted to make dinner. We would often get an appetizer, split a dinner and than dessert. It was a reasonable way to get a nice dinner within walking distance.
More of an upscale Italian restaurant in Edgdewater.  I usually get their Mussels, Insalata Caprese and Penne con Asparagi.  They have daily specials that are hard to refuse.
Just moved to the area and this is a great sport for lunch and dinner. They also do a great gluten free menu.
110 for three people, I guess mostly drinks. But other then the minestrone. Nothing was special, nor good, I make better food at home. Rosebuds is even better.
I've been a fan of Francesca's since their first restaurant opened on North Clark Street. The Bryn Mawr location is close to my home and the staff is terrific. And...their carpaccio is to die for!
